issue(id="0018" status="open")
  title Make bootstrap converge scrubs-managed guest state
  user-story
    as-a scrubs operator re-bootstrapping long-lived guests
    i-want bootstrap to remove retired scrubs-managed artifacts instead of only layering new files on top
    so-that existing guests converge toward the same declared state as fresh guests and do not accumulate stale compatibility surfaces
  premise.
    Recent scrubs migration work deliberately removed legacy installer
    artifacts from the payload for fresh guests. A re-bootstrap of the real
    `systemd-ts` canary guest showed that the guest still completed bootstrap
    successfully, but retained a stale `~/.local/libexec/scrubs/install-dirty-tools.sh`
    file from an older generation because `guest-apply.sh` currently copies
    payload files additively rather than converging managed directories.

    That behavior is survivable, but it is the wrong long-term model for
    scrubs-owned state. If a path is declared and managed by scrubs, bootstrap
    should be able to remove artifacts that are no longer part of the desired
    guest shape. Otherwise long-lived guests become pets, stale compatibility
    files linger indefinitely, and fresh-guest validation stops telling the
    full truth about upgraded guests.

    At the same time, scrubs should not blindly delete everything under a
    guest home directory. The intended model is an explicit preservation
    policy: keep a small allowlist of durable operator state such as project
    working trees and Codex chat/session state on a best-effort basis, while
    applying an iron-fist convergence policy to scrubs-managed subtrees like
    `~/.local/libexec/scrubs` and other directories scrubs claims as declared
    configuration.
  acceptance-criteria
    criterion Scrubs documents which guest-home paths are treated as exact managed state, which are preserved by explicit allowlist, and which remain out of scope.
    criterion Re-bootstrapping an existing guest removes retired scrubs-managed payload files such as deleted helper scripts from exact managed directories.
    criterion Fresh guests and upgraded guests converge on the same scrubs-managed file set for directories claimed as exact state.
    criterion The convergence policy preserves explicitly allowed durable operator state such as project working trees and Codex chat/session history during repeat bootstrap.
    criterion Validation includes at least one re-bootstrap of an existing long-lived canary guest in addition to disposable-guest testing, so migration behavior is exercised directly.
  review-items
    item(status="open").
      Decide which guest-home paths scrubs should treat as exact managed
      subtrees versus explicitly preserved operator state.
    item(status="open").
      Decide whether the safest implementation shape is exact directory sync
      for a few owned paths, a generated manifest of managed files, or some
      combination of those approaches.
